      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Grid convergence index (GCI) or Richardson extrapolation demonstrates discretization error below 5% for the primary QoI (scalar shear stress).",
      "rationale": "A three-level mesh refinement study (3.1M, 8.4M, 22.7M cells) was conducted at the highest-hemolysis operating point. GCI for volume-averaged scalar shear stress is 2.8%, within the 5% acceptance threshold. The medium mesh (8.4M cells) is adopted for the production runs as the optimal accuracy-cost trade-off."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
