      "rationale": "Bench test conditions (flow rate, rotational speed, fluid temperature, hematocrit) are recorded at each of the 5 operating points. Inlet velocity profiles and outlet pressure boundary conditions are derived directly from the experimental measurements. Uncertainty in measured flow rate is ±1.5%, which is propagated into the boundary condition specification."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Predicted RH index agrees with experimental measurements within combined simulation and experimental uncertainty bands at all 5 operating points.",
      "rationale": "Predicted RH index falls within the experimental uncertainty band (±12%) at 4 of 5 operating points. At the fifth point (3.5 L/min, 3600 RPM), the model overpredicts RH by 14%, which is within the expanded uncertainty when measurement repeatability is included. Overall agreement is judged adequate for MRL 2 purposes."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
