      "acceptanceCriteria": "The QoIs computed by the model (RH index, scalar shear stress distribution) directly support the COU decision criterion.",
      "rationale": "The primary QoI is the relative hemolysis index (RH), computed from the power-law hemolysis model integrated along Lagrangian particle trajectories. This quantity directly maps to the regulatory acceptance criterion (RH < 1 relative to predicate device). Secondary QoI (volume-averaged scalar shear stress) supports interpretation of regional hemolysis risk."
